          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-086-404P-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-404P-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-404P-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>hen mother Clud had rose from play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-2" n="2">And call'd to take the Cards away</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-3" n="3">Van saw but seem'd not to regard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-4" n="4">How Miss pick't ev'ry painted Card</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-5" n="5">And busy both with hand, &amp; Eye</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-6" n="6">Soon rear'd a House two Story's high</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-7" n="7">Van's Genius (without thought or Lecture)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-8" n="8">This highly turn'd to Architecture</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-9" n="9">He saw the Edifice and Smil'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-10" n="10">Vow'd it was pretty for a Child</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-11" n="11">It was so perfect in it's kind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-12" n="12">He kept the Model in his mind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-13" n="13">But when he found the Boys at play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-14" n="14">And saw them dabbling in their Clay</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-15" n="15">He stood behind a Stall to lurk</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-16" n="16">And mark the progress of their Work</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-17" n="17">With true delight observ'd 'em all</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-18" n="18">Raking up Mudd to build a Wall</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-19" n="19">The plan he much admir'd &amp; took</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-20" n="20">The Model in his Table-book</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-21" n="21">Thought himself now exactly Skill'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-22" n="22">And so resolv'd a House to build</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-23" n="23">A real House w<hi rend="superscript">thÌ£</hi> Rooms &amp; Stairs</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-24" n="24">Five times at least as big as theirs</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-25" n="25">Taller than Misses by Two yards</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-26" n="26">Not a sham thing of Clay, or Cards</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-27" n="27">And So he did for in a While</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-28" n="28">He built up Such a monstrous Pile</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-29" n="29">That no two Chairmen could be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-30" n="30">Able to lift it from the Ground</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-31" n="31">Still at Whitehall it stands in view</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-32" n="32">Just in the place where first it grew</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-33" n="33">There all the little Schoolboys run</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-34" n="34">Envying to see themselves outdone</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-35" n="35">From such deep rudiments as these</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-36" n="36">Van is become by due degrees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-37" n="37">For building fam'd &amp; justly reckon'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-38" n="38">At Court Vitruvius the second</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-39" n="39">No Wonder! Since wise authors Show</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-40" n="40">That best foundations should be low</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-41" n="41">And now the Duke has wisely ta'ne him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-42" n="42">To be his Architect at Blenheim</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-43" n="43">But raillery for once apart</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-44" n="44">If this rule holds in ev'ry Art</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-45" n="45">Or if his Grace were no more skill'd in</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-46" n="46">The Art of Batt'ring Walls than building</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-47" n="47">We might expect to find next year</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-404P-line-48" n="48">A Mouse-Trapman Chief Engineer.</l>
          </lg>
